SIMPLE: planter
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Planter
<hw>Plant"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, plants or sows; <as>as, a <ex>planter</ex>of corn; a
machine <ex>planter</ex>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who owns or cultivates a plantation; <as>as, a
sugar <ex>planter</ex>; a coffee <ex>planter</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A colonist in a new or uncultivated territory;
<as>as, the first <ex>planters</ex> in Virginia</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>a movable box or a fixed low, open structure, as of
brick, in which plants are grown for decorative purposes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plantership</ent>⟦br⟧
